# Copy to `.env` for local development (never commit `.env`).
# Vite loads `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.[mode].local` — see Vite docs.
#
# LOVABLE / TEAM NOTE:
# - Lovable injects Supabase (and other) secrets in *their* hosted build; the repo
#   does not need a committed `.env` for Lovable to work.
# - If the app breaks in Lovable after gitignore/env changes, check Lovable
#   project Settings → Secrets / Environment — repaste keys from Supabase if needed.
# - Rotating the Supabase anon ("publishable") key in Supabase invalidates the old
#   key; update Lovable secrets AND every developer’s local `.env` to match.

VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_INSTRUCTOR_PIN=
